.SH "NAME"
register_netdevice \- register a network device
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'int\ register_netdevice('u
.BI "int register_netdevice(struct\ net_device\ *\ " "dev" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIdev\fR
.RS 4
device to register
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
Take a completed network device structure and add it to the kernel interfaces\&. A
\fBNETDEV_REGISTER\fR
message is sent to the netdev notifier chain\&. 0 is returned on success\&. A negative errno code is returned on a failure to set up the device, or if the name is a duplicate\&.
.PP
Callers must hold the rtnl semaphore\&. You may want
\fBregister_netdev\fR
instead of this\&.
.PP
BUGS: The locking appears insufficient to guarantee two parallel registers will not get the same name\&.
